truck,
after
an
unnerving
pause
atop
the
bank
ramp,
had
moved
on,
snaking
left
and
right
for
a
minute
or
two,
and
was
now
accelerating
to
what
felt
like
top
speed.
Beneath
them,
the
bulletproof
tires
hummed
on
smooth
pavement.
Forcing
his
attention
to
the
rosewood
box
in
his
arms,
Langdon
laid
the
precious
bundle
on
the
floor,
unwrapped
his
